CISA Alert Advisory on Spring4Shell zero-day vulnerability: https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/alerts/2022/04/01/spring-releases-security-updates-addressing-spring4shell-and-spring-cloud-function-vulnerabilities

CVE Advisory on Spring4Shell zero-day vulnerability: <https://spring.io/security/cve-2022-22965>

Summary:
Spring4Shell (CVE-2022-22965)
- Vulnerability Type: This is a Remote Code Execution (RCE) vulnerability found in the Spring Framework.
- Affected Systems: It impacts applications using Spring MVC or Spring WebFlux that are running on JDK 9 or newer. The most common exploit involves applications deployed as a WAR file on Apache Tomcat.
- Affected Versions: Spring Framework versions 5.3.0 to 5.3.17 and 5.2.0 to 5.2.19 are vulnerable, along with older, unsupported versions.
- Mitigation: Users are strongly advised to update to Spring Framework 5.3.18+ or 5.2.20+ immediately to fix the issue.

Spring Cloud Function Vulnerability (CVE-2022-22963)
- Vulnerability Type: This is also a Remote Code Execution (RCE) vulnerability, but it affects the Spring Cloud Function library.
- Mitigation: The CISA alert recommends that users and administrators apply the necessary security updates released by Spring to address both the "Spring4Shell" and Spring Cloud Function vulnerabilities promptly.
